X=\begin{pmatrix}x_1 \\ x_2 \end{pmatrix} \in M_{2,1}(\mathbb{R})
t_a\rho_{\theta}{t_a}^{-1}(X)
{t_a}^{-1}(X)=\begin{pmatrix}x_1-1 \\ x_2-1 \end{pmatrix}=X'
\rho_{\theta}(X')=\begin{pmatrix}0 & -1 \\ 1 & 0 \end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}x_1-1 \\ x_2-1 \end{pmatrix}= \begin{pmatrix}1- x_2 \\ x_1-1 \end{pmatrix}=X"
t_a(X")=\begin{pmatrix}1- x_2 \\ x_1-1 \end{pmatrix}+\begin{pmatrix}1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}= \begin{pmatrix}2- x_2 \\ x_1 \end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}0 & -1 \\ 1 & 0 \end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}x_1 \\ x_2 \end{pmatrix}+ \begin{pmatrix}2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}
s=t_a\rho_{\theta}
